 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 15: WITNESS PAIRING IS A UAQ INSTANCE. The witness gap (32/272 = 12% coverage) is not a special problem requiring a special solution. It is ANOTHER instance of the universal acquisition function. \n\nA proposed witness pairing is a CONTEXT BLOCK: 'Test test_merge_commutativity likely witnesses INV-MERGE-001 because both reference set-union ordering.' This block has: impact = F(S) improvement from confirming the pairing (one more witnessed INV). cost = agent attention tokens to review and confirm/reject. alpha = impact / cost.\n\nThe hypothesis ledger tracks whether the agent CONFIRMED the pairing. Confirmed = hypothesis correct (the test does witness the INV). Rejected = hypothesis wrong (false positive). The acquisition function learns which test-INV similarity signals predict correct pairings.\n\nTHIS MEANS: the UAQ doesn't just unify five recommendation systems. It unifies ALL information-selection problems in the system. Witness pairing, task routing, context projection, ceremony adaptation, harvest timing — they're all 'which information should I present to maximize ΔF(S) per token?'\n\nThe witness gap resolves itself over time: each session, the acquisition function proposes the highest-alpha witness pairings. The agent confirms or rejects. The calibration improves. After 10 sessions, most high-confidence pairings are confirmed and F(S) reflects real coverage.\n\nThis is the observation-projection duality at the verification layer: tests are observations of invariant behavior. Witnesses are projections of those observations onto the spec graph. The acquisition function optimizes the projection.\n\nSPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-025, ADR-FOUNDATION-028, INV-WITNESS-011."
